This unit is the epitome of what one would expect to see at the Hollywood Riviera, one of West Hollywood's most iconic and architecturally significant condo properties. This stunning 1954 mid-century modern masterpiece was designed by renowned architect Edward Fickett AIA and has been featured in many TV shows, movies, and commercials. This unique and open city loft-style space with high pitched beamed ceilings is in a convenient and coveted location with pool views from the front and some city and hill views from the back. This unit was altered to function as a studio which could easily be converted back to a one-bedroom with updated bathroom, massive walk-in closet and separate kitchen with window overlooking pool. This condo also has central AC, low HOA dues including EQ insurance, and building is Mills Act approved.

1400 N Hayworth Ave #27 is a condo in West Hollywood, CA 90046. This 614 square foot condo sits on a 0.69 acre lot and features 1 bedroom and 1 bathroom. This condo has been listed on Redfin since September 25, 2020 and is currently priced at $539,000. This property was built in 1954. Based on Redfin's West Hollywood data, we estimate the home's value is $538,567, which is 0.1% less than its current list price. Comparable nearby homes include 1318 N Crescent Heights Blvd #208, 1275 Havenhurst Dr #10, and 1345 N Hayworth Ave #101. According to Redfin's Rental Estimate, we expect that this home would rent for between $1,684 and $2,149. Nearby schools include Larchmont Charter School, West Hollywood College Prep School and West Hollywood College Preparatory School. The closest grocery stores are Bristol Farms Hollywood, Trader Joe's and Whole Foods. Nearby coffee shops include The Coffee Bean and Tea Leaf, Cafe If and Enigma Coffee. Nearby restaurants include The Griddle Cafe, Pace Joint and Rock House Sliders. 1400 N Hayworth Ave #27 is near Plummer Park. This address can also be written as 1400 North Hayworth Avenue Apartment 27, West Hollywood, California 90046.
